                            <comment id="14718168" author="dlong" created="Wed, 30 Oct 2024 20:20:11 -0700"  >[~mbaesken], I think it would indeed be useful on those other platforms.  In hindsight, I could have pinged and gotten help from the port maintainers on the other platforms when working on the PR.</comment>
                            <comment id="14717579" author="mbaesken" created="Wed, 30 Oct 2024 01:54:51 -0700"  >Hi  [~dlong] , [~dholmes]  this change adjusted  frame os::fetch_frame_from_context(const void* ucVoid)  on linux arrch64, linux x86_64, windows x86_64  to  use os::fetch_frame_from_context(uc).pc(); .&lt;br/&gt;
Is there a reason why it was done only on those platforms and not on others (like bsd_x86, linux-ppc64 etc.)   ?&lt;br/&gt;
Is there no need for it on those platforms or was it just not done because they were seen not so important (or you could not test those)  ?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
